QUALIFICATION: junior subjective synonym of Corydioidea based on the First Reviser Principle of the ICZN Code
AUTHOR: Saussure

QUALIFICATION: junior subjective synonym of Corydiidae. Brunner von Wattenwyl (1865) as First Reviser chose to use Corydiidae (based on Corydiens Saussure, 1864) as the name for the group rather than Polyphagidae (this name was first used in this form by Walker, 1868). Corydiidae was in common usage until Princis incorrectly synonymised it in 1950 (for details see Kevan (1977))
